==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Earthlight
<hw>Earth"light`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>
<def>The sunlight reflected from the earth to the moon, by which we see
faintly, when the moon is near the sun (either before or after new
moon), that part of the moon's disk unillumined by direct sunlight, or
⟦ldquo⟧the old moon in the arms of the new.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earthly</ent>⟦br⟧
